<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/6013887-natalie-chickey"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1529761500i/6013887._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6013887-natalie-chickey">Natalie Chickey</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think it is Shakespeare&apos;s finest work, but, as a high school British literature teacher, I choose to teach Hamlet or Macbeth, as I believe they are <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think it is Shakespeare's finest work, but, as a high school British literature teacher, I choose to teach Hamlet or Macbeth, as I believe they are more approachable for that age group. If I can excite my students to the great works of Shakespeare (and I am sure that I do!), then I know they will pick up Lear on their own!<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
