<div id="review_2890210666" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2890210666" />
    <a title="Amit Mishra" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/66799591-amit-mishra"><img alt="Amit Mishra" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1606112214p2/66799591.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2890210666?book_show_action=true">Jul 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amit Mishra" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amit Mishra" href="/user/show/66799591-amit-mishra">Amit Mishra</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2890210666" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer511056531160793932">King Lear can be read in various ways - as a theological drama, as a philosophical one, as a supreme example of Shakespeare&apos;s intuitive egalitarianism or even as a melodrama lifted towards tragedy only by its superb poetry. It is the most titanic of Shakespeare&apos;s tragedy. </span>
  <span id="freeText511056531160793932" style="display:none">King Lear can be read in various ways - as a theological drama, as a philosophical one, as a supreme example of Shakespeare's intuitive egalitarianism or even as a melodrama lifted towards tragedy only by its superb poetry. It is the most titanic of Shakespeare's tragedy. </span>
  <a data-text-id="511056531160793932" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

